<DOC><DOCNO> AP881013-0137 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-13-88 1327EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-SeaLions     10-13 0191</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Sea Lions,0195</SECOND><HEAD>Mystery Malady Hits Sea Lions</HEAD><DATELINE>SAUSALITO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   California sea lions are threatened bya mysterious illness marked by seizures so violent some have bittenoff teeth, according to the California Marine Mammal Center.   So far, 28 sea lions stricken with the new malady have beenfound on beaches and trucked to the center, located at an old Armyfort in Marin County, said center spokeswoman Mary Jane Schramm.   Twenty of the sick mammals were found on the San Luis ObispoCounty coast while others were scattered as far north as Santa Cruz.   Eight sea lions have died, including one that had a very highlevel of lead in its body.   Schramm said the center is testing for lead poisoning as well asarsenic, cadmimum, copper, iron and zinc. Other tests are designedto find natural toxins or other compounds in the food chain.   The first sick sea lion arrived April 30 at the center, whichwas already packed with sea lions suffering from leptospirosis.Schramm said that 105 sea lions have been diagnosed with thatdisease since June 1, and more than half have died.</TEXT></DOC>